                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d703">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/2625: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-13T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 13, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. Your No. 40, April 8, 1 p.m. You are authorized in your discretion to inform
                    the Financial Adviser that the Department will not object to the omission of
                    Article 36 from the text of the permanent finance law, provided the Haitian
                    Government in a formal exchange of notes, fully confirms the powers of the
                    Financial Adviser as set forth in Article 36 of the draft finance law.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
